The paper deals with the first order theory of structures over graphs and their definability, which falls under the scope of mathematical logic and model theory. Hence, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as likely sub-categories. The paper discusses the definability of graph predicates and arithmetical relations, which relates to computational complexity, indicating cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the definability of graph orders and subgraph orders, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category.
